    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "This can be done in different way:\r\n\r\n- a contract that exposes an ERC20 interface, but that doesn't take custody of the assets. There are some prototypes for such a contract. Some can be found in the other issues of this repo. [I myself wrote one a while back](https://gist.github.com/Amxx/397908c7a6f6c5afcc673577d1901155). This raises a lot of changes about permissions to transfer the assets and event inconsistency\r\n\r\n- a real wrapper, that would take full custody of the underlying ERC1155 token. This is way simpler. It may or may not have a usecase. (UniswapV4?) \r\n\r\nIf what you had in mind is the second option, we could probably built it.\r\n\r\n**Can you tell us more about your usecase for such a contract?**",
