    "body": "> * a real wrapper, that would take full custody of the underlying ERC1155 token. This is way simpler. It may or may not have a usecase. (UniswapV4?)\r\n\r\nIt is actually this case here\r\n\r\nI was in a group discussion about crypto regulation, and for what it is looking like anytime now brazilian regulators will build some decisions around ERC20, but some projects are already build in ERC1155. \r\n\r\nMy idea was to create one wrapper that takes custody of the tokens, the underlying would be definded by the ERC1155 address and the tokenId.\r\n\r\nAfter this I thought about how uniswap and other projects are built upon ERC20 and liked the idea",
